      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CHEEKY MEEKI (2) finished fifth last time at Bendigo but could not have been more impressive before that in her head turning 23.11 win at this track over 410m. Hot win two back and looks the one to beat here. KODA (5) carved over from wide out and boxed on strongly to finish 0.9 lengths away in second (25.43) behind Wanbi at Shepparton. Expected to feature again. PAW YATANA (8) struggled to get involved last start after missing the jump at Geelong, but prior to that won comfortably by 3.5 lengths at Geelong (22.67) beating Quest For Buzz in a Maiden on March 28. Should be in this for a long way. PAW XEROX (7) is building a solid run of minor placings and will play a big role again.",
